<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910329-0027</DOCNO><DOCID>910329-0027.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Talley Industries Inc.:   Earnings for 1990 Restated   To Show $50.2 Million Loss</HL><DATE>03/29/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   TAL</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Talley Industries Inc. said it restated its 1990 earningsto reflect a new, $53 million pretax charge related to realestate holdings, bringing total charges for last year to $80million and total net loss to $50.2 million, or $5.95 ashare.   Talley's 1990 fourth quarter results already had containeda $17.2 million loss, including a $27 million pretax charge.In announcing these developments last month, the company saidit would slash its common stock dividend 60% to five cents ashare from 12.5 cents.</LP><TEXT>   The new write-down will put the company in breach ofcertain loan covenants, and the company said it will meetwith lenders and include a &quot;going concern&quot; qualification inits 1990 financial statements.   William H. Mallender, chairman, said the charge has noimpact on the company's current operating cash flow. Talleyis a maker of high technology and commercial products thatalso has real estate investments in Phoenix and operates athrift in the Los Angeles area, East-West Federal SavingsBank.</TEXT></DOC>